---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Is OX Valid in Words With Friends? — Cross-Platform Word Checker"
  description="Is OX valid in Words With Friends, Scrabble, and other word games? Complete comparison of OX validity, scoring, and strategy across all major platforms."
  keywords="is ox valid words with friends, ox scrabble word, ox wwf, ox word game valid, ox points scrabble, words with friends ox allowed"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Is OX Valid in Words With Friends? — Cross-Platform Word Checker",
    "description": "Is OX valid in Words With Friends, Scrabble, and other word games? Complete comparison of OX validity, scoring, and strategy across all major platforms.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-29",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/is-ox-valid-in-words-with-friends" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is OX a valid word in Words With Friends?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, OX is valid in Words With Friends. It scores 9 points in WWF (O=1, X=8) compared to 9 points in Scrabble (O=1, X=8). OX is accepted in virtually every major word game platform." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is OX valid in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, OX is valid in both TWL (Tournament Word List) and SOWPODS dictionaries. It scores 9 points (O=1, X=8) and is one of the best 2-letter words because it deploys the valuable X tile in just two letters." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What words can you make from OX in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "OX extends to: OXO (10pts), OXEN (11pts), OXES (11pts), OXIDE (13pts), OXBOW (17pts), OXLIP (14pts). You can also front-hook to create BOX (12pts), FOX (13pts), POX (12pts), SOX (10pts), VOX (13pts)." } }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Word Validity</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Is OX Valid in Words With Friends? — Cross-Platform Word Checker</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-29">June 29, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>4 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        OX is one of the most powerful 2-letter words in any word game. At just two tiles, it deploys the X (worth 8 points) instantly. But is it valid everywhere? Short answer: yes. Here's the full breakdown across platforms.
      </p>

      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-green-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-green-950/30 to-emerald-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-green-500/70">✓ Verdict</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">OX — VALID EVERYWHERE</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-green-300 font-semibold mb-3">9 points in Scrabble • 9 points in Words With Friends</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">OX is accepted in Scrabble (TWL + SOWPODS), Words With Friends, Wordfeud, and every major word game app. It's a universal play you can always rely on.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Platform Comparison</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Scrabble (TWL)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid. 9 points. Tournament legal in North America.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Scrabble (SOWPODS)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid. 9 points. International dictionary includes OX.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Words With Friends</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid. 9 points. WWF uses its own dictionary — OX is in it.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Wordfeud / Other Apps</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid in virtually all word game apps. Universal acceptance.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Scoring Differences: Scrabble vs WWF</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Difference</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">While OX scores the same base points (9) in both games, the <span class="text-white font-medium">premium square layouts differ</span>. WWF has different board patterns than Scrabble, so where you place OX matters more than the base score. In WWF, aim for the TL square under the X.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">OX Extensions & Hooks</h2>
      <p>OX is a foundation word. It hooks into dozens of longer plays across all platforms.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BOX</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">12 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FOX</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">POX</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">12 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">VOX</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">OXEN</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">11 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">OXBOW</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">17 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">OXIDE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13 pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips for OX</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Play OX parallel to existing words:</span> Place OX next to a word to create two scoring plays simultaneously. If a word has O or X adjacent, you score both OX and the cross-word in one turn.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">X on premium squares:</span> In both Scrabble and WWF, landing X on a Triple Letter Score gives you 24 points from one tile. OX is short enough to position precisely for premium square access.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Set up front hooks:</span> After playing OX, opponents might extend it — but you can plan for B+OX, F+OX, or V+OX on your next turn for an additional 12-13 points per play.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/is-ox-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is OX a Scrabble Word? — Complete Analysis</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/words-with-friends-vs-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words With Friends vs Scrabble — Key Differences</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/best-two-letter-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best Two-Letter Words in Scrabble</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-blue-800/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Try our free Scrabble Word Finder — instant results, no signup</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-400 text-gray-950 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
